==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Puissant
<hw>Pu"is*sant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., originally, a
p. pr. formed fr. L. <ets>posse</ets> to be able: cf. L.
<ets>potens</ets> powerful. See <er>Potent</er>.]</ety> <def>Powerful;
strong; mighty; forcible; <as>as, a <ex>puissant</ex> prince or
empire</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Puissant</xex> deeds.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of <qex>puissant</qex> nations which the world possessed.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And worldlings in it are less merciful,⟦br⟧
And more <qex>puissant</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puissantly</ent>⟦br⟧
